t: He*p that dwelleth in the secret place of the most High shall abide under the shadow of the Almighty.
I*p will say of the Lord,*s He is my refuge and my fortress: my God; in him will I trust.
Surely*p he shall deliver thee from the snare of the fowler, and from the noisome pestilence.
He*p shall cover thee with his feathers, and under his wings shalt thou trust: his truth shall be thy shield and buckler.
Thou*p shalt not be afraid for the terror by night; nor for the arrow that flieth by day;
Nor*p for the pestilence that walketh in darkness; nor for the destruction that wasteth at noonday.
A*p thousand shall fall at thy side, and ten thousand at thy right hand; but it shall not come nigh thee.
Only*p with thine eyes shalt thou behold and see the reward of the wicked.
Because*p thou hast made the Lord,*s which is my refuge, even the most High, thy habitation;
There*p shall no evil befall thee, neither shall any plague come nigh thy dwelling.
For*p he shall give his angels charge over thee, to keep thee in all thy ways.
They*p shall bear thee up in their hands, lest thou dash thy foot against a stone.
Thou*p shalt tread upon the lion and adder: the young lion and the dragon shalt thou trample under feet.
Because*p he hath set his love upon me, therefore will I deliver him: I will set him on high, because he hath known my name.
He*p shall call upon me, and I will answer him: I will be with him in trouble; I will deliver him, and honour him.
With*p long life will I satisfy him, and shew him my salvation.
